column5: heading out onto simcoe for the first time ever on saturday. we are targeting whitefish/lake trout (hoping to catch my first of each.) are plan is to just head towards ice huts and hope for best. were should we launch from? we are coming from lindsay side i think it come out near beaverton any ideas?
Not too familiar with your side of the lake but it's been beyond mild here in Barrie and the ice on most of the laker areas just formed last week. Keep checking for ice reports.
most of the laker fishing happens on the west side of the lake
While rounding the Barrie lakeshore,some open water near the area where the water returns to the lake..The big open water may have taken a bit of a hit the last two days?,not sure but be careful.
